atmPortStatEntry.name: atmPortStatEntry
atmPortStatEntry.description: ATM Port Statistics. Each entry is indexed by two fields: The card number and the port number.

atmStatCardId.name: atmStatCardId
atmStatCardId.description: This field is the card index

atmStatPortId.name: atmStatPortId
atmStatPortId.description: This field is the port index

atmSigDetected.name: atmSigDetected
atmSigDetected.description: This bit field indicates if the port receives signal from the remote ATM port. 1= signal present, 2= no signal.

atmRxBadHecCell.name: atmRxBadHecCell
atmRxBadHecCell.description: The number of cells received that has a bad ATM cell header (HEC). The error is usually due to a physical layer problem. For example, when the fiber is first connected to the system or a clock mismatch.

atmRxDmaDropCell.name: atmRxDmaDropCell
atmRxDmaDropCell.description: The number of cells received but is discarded by the ATM header validation checking. The error is usually due to a incorrectly configured VPI/VCI or other configuration error.

atmRxGoodCell.name: atmRxGoodCell
atmRxGoodCell.description: The number of cells received that is valid.

atmTxDmaDropCell.name: atmTxDmaDropCell
atmTxDmaDropCell.description: The number of outgoing cells dropped due to congestions.

atmSuniFifoOverrun.name: atmSuniFifoOverrun
atmSuniFifoOverrun.description: The number of times that the SUNI FIFO overrun status bit has been read in the true state.

atmElanPvcStatisticEntry.name: atmElanPvcStatisticEntry
atmElanPvcStatisticEntry.description: ATM Elan PVC statistics. The Elan ID is used as the index of the object.

atmElanPvcInUcastPkt.name: atmElanPvcInUcastPkt
atmElanPvcInUcastPkt.description: The number of unicast packet that is received from this Elan PVC.

atmElanPvcInMcastPkt.name: atmElanPvcInMcastPkt
atmElanPvcInMcastPkt.description: The number of multicast packet that is received from this Elan PVC.

atmElanPvcOutUcastPkt.name: atmElanPvcOutUcastPkt
atmElanPvcOutUcastPkt.description: The number of unicast packet that is transmitted from this Elan PVC.

atmElanPvcOutMcastPkt.name: atmElanPvcOutMcastPkt
atmElanPvcOutMcastPkt.description: The number of unicast packet that is transmitted from this Elan PVC.

atmPvcStatusEntry.name: atmPvcStatusEntry
atmPvcStatusEntry.description: ATM PVC status. The PVC circuit ID is used as the index of the object.

atmPvcCktId.name: atmPvcCktId
atmPvcCktId.description: This field is the index of the circuit.

atmPvcElanId.name: atmPvcElanId
atmPvcElanId.description: This field is the index of the elan this circuit belongs to.

atmPvcRemoteSwitchInfoValid.name: atmPvcRemoteSwitchInfoValid
atmPvcRemoteSwitchInfoValid.description: This field is based on the aging timer of a remote switch. If the local switch has not received any packets from the remote switch for a period of time, then it is declared as non-valid. 1 = non-valid 2 = valid (normal state of operation).

atmPvcRemoteSwitchMacAddress.name: atmPvcRemoteSwitchMacAddress
atmPvcRemoteSwitchMacAddress.description: This field lists the remote switch's MAC address. If the atmInterSwitchPvcRemoteSwitchInfoValid object is 1, then this field contains the valid info. Otherwise, this field contains the last learned info.

atmPvcRemoteSwitchPvcStatus.name: atmPvcRemoteSwitchPvcStatus
atmPvcRemoteSwitchPvcStatus.description: This field is set if the remote switch receives packets from this switch. If atmInterSwitchPvcRemoteSwitchInfoValid objeect is 1, then this field contains the valid info. Otherwise, this field contains the last learned info.

atmPvcSTPState.name: atmPvcSTPState
atmPvcSTPState.description: This field indicates the STP port state of the circuit.

atmPvcRemoteElanId.name: atmPvcRemoteElanId
atmPvcRemoteElanId.description: This field indicates the elan ID of the circuit.

atmPvcRemoteMcpIpAddress.name: atmPvcRemoteMcpIpAddress
atmPvcRemoteMcpIpAddress.description: This is the remote mcp ip address.

cnCurPtptConns.name: cnCurPtptConns
cnCurPtptConns.description: This counter counts the number of current point-to-point calls of the switch.

cnCurPtmptConns.name: cnCurPtmptConns
cnCurPtmptConns.description: This counter counts the number of current point-to-multipoint calls of the switch.

cnCurActiveConns.name: cnCurActiveConns
cnCurActiveConns.description: This counter counts the number of current active calls of the switch.

cnCurPortConnsTable.name: cnCurPortConnsTable
cnCurPortConnsTable.description: This table contains the point-to-point, point-to-multipoint and active calls per port for all the atm ports in the switch.

cnCurPortConnsEntry.name: cnCurPortConnsEntry
cnCurPortConnsEntry.description: This entry contains the point-to-point, point-to-multipoint and active calls per port.

cnCurPortConnsPtptConns.name: cnCurPortConnsPtptConns
cnCurPortConnsPtptConns.description: This entry counts the number of current point-to-point calls per port.

cnCurPortConnsPtmptConns.name: cnCurPortConnsPtmptConns
cnCurPortConnsPtmptConns.description: This entry counts the number of current point-to-multipoint calls per port.

cnCurPortConnsActiveConns.name: cnCurPortConnsActiveConns
cnCurPortConnsActiveConns.description: This entry counts the number of current active calls per port.

atmCardOperEntry.name: atmCardOperEntry
atmCardOperEntry.description: ATM Card Operational values. Each entry is indexed by card number

atmCardOperCardId.name: atmCardOperCardId
atmCardOperCardId.description: This field is the card index

atmCardOperExtClockSource.name: atmCardOperExtClockSource
atmCardOperExtClockSource.description: This field indicates the operational external clock source. The following value is read-only: 0 = Local Oscillator, 1..N = ATM port id for external clock source. This object only applies to ATM MDA modules with SM, MM, or UTP media types.

cnStsEnqPTPCalls.name: cnStsEnqPTPCalls
cnStsEnqPTPCalls.description: The number of current point-to-point calls in the status enquiry queue of the switch.

cnStsEnqActiveParties.name: cnStsEnqActiveParties
cnStsEnqActiveParties.description: The number of current active parties in the status enquiry queue of the switch. (This includes point- to-multi-point calls).

cnStsEnqSent.name: cnStsEnqSent
cnStsEnqSent.description: The total number of status enquiry requests sent.

cnStsEnqCfmsRecvd.name: cnStsEnqCfmsRecvd
cnStsEnqCfmsRecvd.description: The number of current status messages (in response to status enquiry) received.

cnStsEnqRetried.name: cnStsEnqRetried
cnStsEnqRetried.description: The total number of status enquiry commands retried.

cnStsEnqTimeOuts.name: cnStsEnqTimeOuts
cnStsEnqTimeOuts.description: The total number of status enquiry commands timed out i.e The number of calls for which status (in response to status enquiry) was not received.

cnStsEnqQueueSize.name: cnStsEnqQueueSize
cnStsEnqQueueSize.description: The size of the status enquiry queue.

cnStsEnqCallsCleared.name: cnStsEnqCallsCleared
cnStsEnqCallsCleared.description: The number of calls cleared by status enquiry.
